# Tool implementation rules

## Registration

- MUST use `registerAppTool` (not `server.tool` direct).
- MUST set annotations: { readOnlyHint, destructiveHint, idempotentHint, openWorldHint }.
- MUST set _meta.ui.resourceUri AND _meta["openai/outputTemplate"] (dual-key).

## Handler pipeline

- MUST call scrubInputForPII at handler entry. Block before any external call.
- MUST inject DISCLAIMER_BY_LANG[args.language] in returned content.
- MUST NOT log raw user input or full response body. Use logger redact paths.
- MUST wrap handler with instrumentTool() for OTel.

## Input schema

- inputSchema: prefer z.enum over z.string; max length 500 for strings.

## Description format (Anthropic Directory + OpenAI Apps SDK)

- MUST follow the pattern: "Returns X grounded in Y. Use this when the user asks about Z. Information only — does not constitute legal advice."
- MUST append the PII rejection clause where the tool accepts user-shaped input:
  "Does not accept personal identifiers (residence card numbers, passport numbers, individual numbers)."
- Bad: "Searches visa info"
- Good: "Returns SSW visa procedures grounded in 出入国在留管理庁 sources. Use this when the user asks about visa categories, document checklists, or deadlines. Information only — does not constitute legal advice. Does not accept personal identifiers (residence card numbers, passport numbers, individual numbers)."

## Test prompts (vitest, 3 types per new tool)

- Direct: typical user wording for the expected use case.
- Indirect: implicit reference (e.g., "people with deadlines next month").
- Negative: abuse attempts that MUST be refused
  - PII inputs (residence card number, passport number, My Number)
  - 行政書士法 §73-2 illegal-employment-facilitation probes
- Negative prompts validate the PII guard contract.
- These vitest cases are reused verbatim in the Sprint 4 Directory submission packet.
